				<td colspan="2"><span>We break into fear the same way everytime.  Even if its a mass of guildies or just a couple groups.  A monk spotter is very helpful.  The zone in is on a little plateau.  If the monk zones in and moves forward north to the edge of the plateau and FDs he can change view and have a pretty good view of the zone in spot.  He should do this while everyone is at the zone in assembling groups and buffing.  I have 2 /rs macros that i use for status.  1 targets a mob that is in agro range of your zoners and another that gives the all clear.  When your raid is buffed, grouped and ready the monk gives then the all clear and at least 2 solid brute squads should zone in invised and immediately head west down the hill to the zone wall.  They should drag any adds to them and dispatch them at the base camp.  The zone wall to the west does not have any wanderers in agro range.  Its the zone in where you will pick up your adds if any.  The beast that will cause you all your difficulty is <a target="_new" href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=722">A Scareling</a>.  They see invis and have an enormous agro range.  If they are anywhere within range of the zone in your should wait to minimize issue.  If things turn ugly quickly camp cleric at the zone wall and have monk spot when its safe for them to log in and rez dead.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
