				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Fear<a name="27303"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 12 04 1:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A bard in their 60's can easily break fear solo, even with the berserker epic mob there.  The berserker mob only changed my spot, not the tactic.  
<br />

<br />
Zone in and run to south wall.  You'll probably agro several critters.  Just chant kite them one by one until you're done, then the rest of the raid can come in unmolested.  This takes a great deal of time, so start an hour or so before raid time.  I go for the little frogs first since they cast a short fear spell.  In my way-too-many-times of doing this, the fear has only landed once, but why take chances, just kill them first, then move on to the non-casters.  
<br />

<br />
You can solo any mob in the zone this way except the demis, the berserker epic mob, and CT himself.  It takes ages and gets boring fast, but is doable.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
