<br />
There are some charmable and some uncharmable mobs there.  By doing all chants I don't have to mess with which are and are not charmable.  I'm just that lazy.  
<br />

<br />
On a secondary note (and I might be completely off here), I recall hearing that there is a mob that will shadowstep/gate its target.  If I have something charmed and it shadowsteps/gates a mob out of my normal chase range (or is the target of said shadowstep/gate) it will pass agro around and eventually get my DT'ed by the demi's.  I just bypass this by not charming.  </span></td>
